    <div class="nhsuk-a-z-list--results-items">
      <h2 id="W">W</h2>
      <h3 id="walk-in-centre">walk-in centre</h3>
      <p>Not walk in centre or Walk-In Centre (unless it’s the name of a particular centre).</p>
      <h3 id="water-infections">water infections</h3>
      <p>We use "urinary tract infections (UTIs)" instead.</p>
      <h3 id="water-tablets">water tablets</h3>
      <p>We don’t use "water tablets". We explain that diuretics are "tablets that make you pee more".</p>
      <h3 id="wellbeing">wellbeing</h3>
      <p>One word. </p>
      <h3 id="wind">wind</h3>
      <p>We use "wind" when we're talking about babies. For example, "bringing up wind".</p>
      <p>We also use it when we're talking about "trapped wind" or bloating.</p>
      <p>We use "burping" too.</p>
      <p>Also see "<a href="#fart">fart</a>".</p>
